01/05/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Police at the Serbian-Hungarian border have detained two people for allegedly trying to cross the border illegally, one of whom may be a member of the Turkish Hezbollah group sentenced to life in prison for terrorist attacks in Turkey.
Interior Minister Ivica Dacic announced on Saturday (April 30th) that police have sent copies of documents and fingerprints to Turkish authorities to verify the suspects' identities.
(Beta, B92, Tanjug, Radio Free Europe - 30/04/11)
